## Description

Fixes #7890 7890

Note: It's a good idea to open an issue first for discussion.

## Checklist
- [x] I have followed [Sample Guidelines from AUTHORING_GUIDE.MD](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/main/AUTHORING_GUIDE.md)
- [x] README is updated to include [all relevant information](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/main/AUTHORING_GUIDE.md#readme-file)
- [ ] **Tests** pass:   `nox -s py-3.6` (see [Test Environment Setup](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/main/AUTHORING_GUIDE.md#test-environment-setup))
- [ ] **Lint** pass:   `nox -s lint` (see [Test Environment Setup](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/main/AUTHORING_GUIDE.md#test-environment-setup))
- [ ] These samples need a new **API enabled** in testing projects to pass (let us know which ones)
- [ ] These samples need a new/updated **env vars** in testing projects set to pass (let us know which ones)
- [x] Please **merge** this PR for me once it is approved.
- [x] This sample adds a new sample directory, and I updated the [CODEOWNERS file](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/main/.github/CODEOWNERS) with the codeowners for this sample

pull_request.title: Airflow summit dag
pull_request.body:
## Description
This PR has

- A Dag file + test
- A data processing file used with dataproc + test
- a constraints file which is a best practice for installing Airflow dags (I forgot to have @PeWu include it in his earlier PR)
- A small CSV of test data derived from licensed data + 
### The DAG

The DAG goes through the following steps:

- Ingests a CSV from GCS into BigQuery Table
- Joins the data from that CSV with a dataset in BigQuery Public Datasets
- Runs a Dataproc job to process data in the joined dataset using Dataproc Serverless
- Outputs that data into BigQuery (we can also output it into GCS if that makes more sense)

The data join job runs once for every table we use in BQ Public datasets using the technique (for-loop) outlined in [the docs](https://airflow.apache.org/docs/apache-airflow/2.3.0/concepts/dags.html#dynamic-dags) and using a [TaskGroup](https://airflow.apache.org/docs/apache-airflow/2.0.0/concepts.html#taskgroup)

### Data processing
The data processing file has a single functiont hat takes data in a BQ dataset column that represents 10ths of a degree celsius and multiplies it by 10, converting it to degrees celsius. It puts those results in the same column in a new dataset

## Checklist
- [ ] I have followed [Sample Guidelines from AUTHORING_GUIDE.MD](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/main/AUTHORING_GUIDE.md)
- [ ] README is updated to include [all relevant information](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/main/AUTHORING_GUIDE.md#readme-file)
- [ ] **Tests** pass:   `nox -s py-3.6` (see [Test Environment Setup](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/main/AUTHORING_GUIDE.md#test-environment-setup))
- [ ] **Lint** pass:   `nox -s lint` (see [Test Environment Setup](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/main/AUTHORING_GUIDE.md#test-environment-setup))
- [ ] These samples need a new **API enabled** in testing projects to pass (let us know which ones)
- [ ] These samples need a new/updated **env vars** in testing projects set to pass (let us know which ones)
- [ ] Please **merge** this PR for me once it is approved.
- [ ] This sample adds a new sample directory, and I updated the [CODEOWNERS file](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/python-docs-samples/blob/main/.github/CODEOWNERS) with the codeowners for this sample
